You have everything you
need right in front of you,

1:21:01.304 --> 1:21:05.930
and I, well, I am
needed elsewhere.

1:21:08.760 --> 1:21:11.245
I chose you because the
work is personal to you,

1:21:12.419 --> 1:21:15.215
and when it's personal,
you see it through,

1:21:15.249 --> 1:21:18.597
and, despite others trying
to beat it out of you,

1:21:18.632 --> 1:21:21.048
you haven't lost
your sense of wonder

1:21:21.083 --> 1:21:22.739
and your zeal for discovery.

1:21:24.465 --> 1:21:27.572
I'm going to guess that
when I push out in a moment,

1:21:27.606 --> 1:21:28.884
our sensory-enabled
friends are going

1:21:28.918 --> 1:21:30.920
to be the first to
notice and probably

1:21:30.955 --> 1:21:32.749
the first to start out after me.

1:21:35.097 --> 1:21:37.478
Let them be your guide
as you take this work

1:21:37.513 --> 1:21:40.412
further than I could
have ever imagined.

1:21:41.931 --> 1:21:43.243
By now, you may have figured out

1:21:43.277 --> 1:21:45.038
you just had your
first experience

1:21:45.072 --> 1:21:46.280
with the multiplier effect,

1:21:47.488 --> 1:21:49.490
those senses layered
on top of one another

1:21:49.525 --> 1:21:52.010
to reveal the sixth sense,

1:21:53.011 --> 1:21:55.186
which is ultimately
our shared humanity.

1:21:56.497 --> 1:21:57.913
You're probably also
thinking that it was

1:21:57.947 --> 1:22:01.123
a failed experiment,
but you're wrong.

1:22:02.158 --> 1:22:04.195
If everyone came
together in that water,

1:22:05.472 --> 1:22:07.957
and if they're standing
beside your right now,

1:22:07.992 --> 1:22:12.548
I can tell you, it succeeded
beyond my wildest dreams.

1:22:14.101 --> 1:22:17.553
Now, take a breath,
and go forward.

1:22:20.314 --> 1:22:21.143
- What's next?

1:22:22.696 --> 1:22:23.524
- [Amberger Voiceover]
You know what to do.

1:22:25.112 --> 1:22:26.976
- We finish the work.

